The preview party of Enchanted at @descansogardens is my favorite event of every year. It brings me enormous joy and is a bright light right as the cold and darkness of winter sets in. This was my first year sponsoring and my best yet due in large part to the brilliant group of humans who joined for a garden frolic. Honored to be a board member and a small part of this incredible organization that beautifully and consistently provides a place to connect with plants and each other. Enchanted runs through January 8th and is a world class, gorgeous and family friendly event that I highly recommend it!

Holidaze dump 💕… Growth happens in the darkness so it’s sacred and shouldn’t go unappreciated but it can be a slog to trudge through this time of year. For centuries humans have celebrated this season by enjoying the winter but also telling it to go the hell away already by looking ahead to more light. Jesus is a nice symbol because he’s a baby, new life, but Kwanzaa, Hanukkah and many ancient witchy winter feasts all get at the same thing: Hope and less darkness. Even a goth like me can get tapped out by the cold night days of winter so I was happy to have lights, feast, fam, friends and laughter. We’ve trudged through the darker days one step and one day at a time. Here’s to more light ahead ✨🌱

The best thing I got out of my 30s was learning to take care of myself and getting comfortable in my own skin. I started them off in a better place than I had been in my 20s but still flinched when I passed mirrors and was sometimes too depressed to scrounge up the energy to brush my teeth. I would get suicidal over something as simple as not being able to find my keys. I thought if I couldn’t do that I didn’t deserve to be here. I let people who weren’t particularly happy tell me what I should do and who I should be. I was sometimes righteous, reckless and often very hard on myself but I was also bright eyed, driven, brave and smart enough to throw myself into creativity, recovery, friendships, pleasure, moving my body and a whole lot of fun adventures. I’m grateful for my life, for the last ten years and how, especially in the last year, I learned to navigate whatever comes and generally stay grounded and true to myself, and found the self worth I needed to enjoy the luxury of taking consistent dental hygiene for granted. Today I want to be alive, even though I still have no idea where I put my damn keys! Maybe I’ll figure that out next decade, maybe not, either way I’m just happy to be here, unflinchingly digging myself, in my birthday suit, starting a new decade. Thanks to everyone who helped get me here ❤️

Hi! It’s #transdayofvisibility Look at me! I’m trans and visible. I used to feel weird about assigned days like this cuz I just want to have every day to fart along with life like everyone else and it took me a bit to realize these are social prompts with the goal of getting us to a point where we can just live like everyone else. Trans folks make up a small percentage of the United States but make up a huge percentage of targeted attacks in legislation and individual violence and harassment. It’s scary. I don’t understand that and have tried to and the best I can come up with is that people can have a real violent fear of what they don’t know. There’s a lot that people don’t know or understand about us and I think that gets entrenched because people also fear making mistakes/looking dumb which is funny because we’re humans so making mistakes and looking dumb sometimes is as guaranteed as death and taxes. So on this day of visibility my wish is that if you’re cis you try to know us better. And if you’re trans my wish is that you be happy and free and keep being visible. I am so grateful for your visibility! Happy #trans day fam!

It’s been a year. I haven’t gotten better at grief but it has helped me to share it and to accept that some days are just awful. I want to write something poetic, funny or celebratory about @mercerbenz . She was hilarious and there’s an infinite amount to celebrate, I mean, look at her! I can’t believe I got to have her as a best friend. I want to say something that finds meaning or a bright side to loss, but all I got is that today sucks. It blows that a whole year can exist without her in it. It sucks that she’d be the best source of comfort when things suck and most of the time she’s the person I want to talk to. And if you knew her or you know grief, maybe you feel similarly? Maybe you don’t, maybe you feel great today, grief is a wild ride so either way if you’re a human who’s lost someone, which is most of us, shout out to you for being here and surviving loss however you are. I was really lucky to know her and I know she’d want everyone to keep it moving and keep glowing and showing up and I will do my best, maybe tomorrow, but today just blows and I miss her

My Da just sent me this picture of my early drag performance as Lady Liberty as a “Father’s Day present”. He’s the sort of dad who enthusiastically celebrates his kids on a day set up to celebrate him because “you can’t have fatherhood without offspring”. He taught me how to walk in heels, how to get up from a pratfall, how to get out of a carriage like the queen, he’s always cheered on any creative or curious impulse I’ve had and has set a great example of how to put on a show and shine bright in the hopes of giving someone, anyone, a bit of light, and how worthwhile that is. Happy Father’s Day, bravissimo!!👏 #edoftheclass

Just read an interesting but also over dramatic Atlantic article about how Social Media is the Tower of Babel and outrage and lack of authenticity, universal truth and connection is destroying our species/society. It was scare mongering but also rang true in parts. This place can be full of highlight reels, not reals, I’m guilty of that. I do like to look on the bright side and go on treasure hunts for joy though and I find a lot of that here. So anyway the real is I’m not great right now, pretty heartbroken at the moment, life has been tough for the last year and a half but also full of fun, great stuff and love. This rose knocked my socks off and will wither away soon. I imagine it will be content just having bloomed. Every rose that follows from this bush will carry a bit of it. Tomorrow’s another day, this evening will likely be another feeling. There is no sound more hilarious than a fart and that’s the most likely last sound any human makes at the end of our life. I love the old timey term “gas” to describe fun. Even when I’m down I still have hope that I’ll fill up with gas til my last gasp. How are you?

On July 10th 2005 at around 10:45pm I had already drank a quarter handle of vodka and was driving to a bar. I thought I was in a pretty good mood, considering. I had on a nice dress and had big plans to get wasted, get laid, then off myself. I was miserable and hopeless but just drunk and desperate enough to stop at this intersection and make a deal with God that if they gave me a sign by the time the light turned green I’d finally get sober. I turned my head, not to the liquor store on the right, but to the left, and realized my car was right outside of an AA meeting that was about to start. My exact reaction was “fuck.” But I’m glad I went in. It has been 18 years of strangers who are family teaching me how to live and be kinder to myself and others, bit by bit. This year has taught me I can stay sober through anything and face whatever comes with solutions, community and a foundation of serenity. If I wake up sober tomorrow my sobriety will be old enough to vote. I cannot believe I’m still alive, still sober, and I’m just so happy and grateful to be here. Thank you to Bill and all his friends for giving me a life beyond my wildest

A true patron saint of Ireland. The Ireland I partly grew up in was beautiful in many ways but steeped in a culture of silence and abuse. People called her crazy for telling the truth. They called her crazy as if that was the worst thing she could be. Institutionalized rape and abuse on a global scale in the largest church in the world was deemed more sane than she was. No one talked about it. People let children get raped by priests rather than address it. If that’s not insane I don’t know what is. But she talked about it. In a culture and a country that constantly told us to shut up and disappear she never stopped talking. I never met her but I was a kid who desperately needed her to survive. She gave me a voice just by using her own.

social_posts.post_text: Rewatched one of my favorite films, @alainberliner_official ‘s My Life in Pink (1997) and it filled my brain and heart to bursting. I watched it 4 times on the big screen as a kid which involved begging adults to get me to the theatre. I was captivated. It was the first time I saw myself on screen. I looked nothing like little Ludo, we were different in many ways, but I felt like her. It’s a funny, heart wrenching and hopeful film with brilliant visual storytelling (most recently homaged by Greta Gerwig in @barbiethemovie ) and every character is afforded a full range of flaws and human complications to work through. This viewing left me struck with so much tenderness for how we’re all scared children no matter how grown up we think we are and how fantasy and dreams aren’t just an escape, sometimes they’re a life line and the only place we can authentically be ourselves. The more we afford ourselves the space to dream and carry those dreams into the world, the happier we all are 💖#queercinema #lgbtqcinema #queerfilm
